[src:chemical-equilibrium/chemical-equilibrium] If there are a total of *k* types of atoms in the system, then there will be *k* such equations.
[src:chemical-equilibrium/chemical-equilibrium] If ions are involved, an additional row is added to the aij matrix specifying the respective charge on each molecule which will sum to zero.
[src:chemical-equilibrium/chemical-equilibrium] This is a standard problem in optimisation, known as constrained minimisation.
[src:chemical-equilibrium/chemical-equilibrium] The most common method of solving it is using the method of Lagrange multipliers (although other methods may be used).
