[src:chemical-equilibrium/chemical-equilibrium] This method of calculating equilibrium chemical concentrations is useful for systems with a large number of different molecules.
[src:chemical-equilibrium/chemical-equilibrium] The use of *k* atomic element conservation equations for the mass constraint is straightforward, and replaces the use of the stoichiometric coefficient equations.
